    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The MACRS depreciation formula for a 7-year property class is: \n\nMACRS Depreciation = (Cost of Equipment - Residual Value) / (Remaining Useful Life x Depreciation Method)\n\nFor the first year, the depreciation rate is 20%. \n\nYou can use the Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System (MACRS) tables to find the exact formula and rates. It's a bit complex, but I can help you with that. \n\nThe MACRS tables show the depreciation rates for each year, and they're based on the number of years remaining in the asset's useful life. Since your equipment is a 7-year property class, the first year's depreciation rate is 20%. \n\nTo calculate the first year's depreciation, you can use the following formula: \n\nFirst Year Depreciation = (Cost of Equipment - Residual Value) x 20%\n\nHowever, if you don't have the residual value, you can use the cost of the equipment as a substitute. \n\nLet's say the cost of the equipment is $100,000. The MACRS tables show that for a 7-year property class, the first year's depreciation rate is 20%. \n\nFirst Year Depreciation = $100,",
